obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (52340)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00046_199707_1613368563388&sectionId=52340&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00046_199707_1613368563388
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Industrial Reconstruction`
  line `Bank (Transfer of Undertakings and Repeal) Act, 1997.`
  line
  line `(2) It shall be deemed to have come into force on the 24th day of January, 1997.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (52341)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00046_199707_1613368563388&sectionId=52341&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00046_199707_1613368563388
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires--`
  line
  line `(a) "appointed day" means such date as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint under section 3;`
  line
  line `(b) "Company" means the Industrial Investment Bank of India Limited to be formed and`
  line `registered under the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956);`
  line
  line `(c) "Reconstruction Bank" means the Industrial Reconstruction Bank of India established under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 3 of the Industrial Reconstruction Bank of India Act, 1984 (62 of 1984).`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (52342)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Undertakings of the Reconstruction Bank to vest in company.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes `1. 27th March, 1997, vide notification No. S.O. 242(E), dated 25th March, 1997, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part II, sec. 3(ii).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00046_199707_1613368563388&sectionId=52342&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00046_199707_1613368563388
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `On such date as the Central`
  line `Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, appoint, there shall be transferred to, and vest`
  line `in, the Company, the undertakings of Reconstruction Bank.`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (52343)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `General effect of vesting of undertaking in Company.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00046_199707_1613368563388&sectionId=52343&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00046_199707_1613368563388
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government, being`
  line `the shareholder of the Reconstruction Bank immediately before the appointed day, shall be deemed to`
  line `be registered, on and from the appointed day, as a shareholder of the Company.`
  line
  line `(2) The undertakings of the Reconstruction Bank which are transferred to, and which vest in, the`
  line `Company under section 3 shall be deemed to include all business, assets, rights, powers, authorities and`
  line `privileges and all properties, movable and immovable, real and personal, corporeal and incorporeal, in`
  line `possession or reservation, present or contingent of whatever nature and wheresoever situate including`
  line `lands, buildings, vehicles, cash balances, deposits, foreign currencies, disclosed and undisclosed`
  line `reserves, reserve fund, special reserve fund, benevolent reserve fund, any other fund, stocks,`
  line `investments, shares, bonds, debentures, security, management of any industrial concern, loans,`
  line `advances and guarantees given to industrial concerns, tenancies, leases and book debts and all other`
  line `rights and interests arising out of such property as were immediately before the appointed day in the`
  line `ownership, possession or power of the Reconstruction Bank in relation to its undertakings, within or`
  line `without India, all books of account, registers, records and documents relating thereto and shall also be`
  line `deemed to include all borrowings, liabilities and obligations of whatever kind within or without India`
  line `then subsisting of the Reconstruction Bank in relation to its undertakings.`
  line
  line `(3) All contracts, deeds, bonds, guarantees, powers of attorney, other instruments and working`
  line `arrangements subsisting immediately before the appointed day and affecting the Reconstruction Bank shall cease to have effect or to be enforceable against the Reconstruction Bank and shall be of as full`
  line `force and effect against or in favour of the Company in which the undertakings of the Reconstruction`
  line `Bank have vested by virtue of this Act and enforceable as fully and effectually as if instead of the`
  line `Reconstruction Bank, the Company had been named therein or had been a party thereto.`
  line
  line `(4) Any proceeding or cause of action pending or existing immediately before the appointed day by`
  line `or against the Reconstruction Bank in relation to its undertakings may, as from the appointed day, be`
  line `continued and enforced by or against the Company in which the undertakings of the Reconstruction`
  line `Bank have vested by virtue of this Act as it might have been enforced by or against the Reconstruction`
  line `Bank if this Act had not been enacted and shall cease to be enforceable by or against the Reconstruction`
  line Bank
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (52344)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Provisions in respect of officers and other employees of Reconstruction Bank.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00046_199707_1613368563388&sectionId=52344&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00046_199707_1613368563388
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every`
  line `officer or other employee of the Reconstruction Bank (except a Director of the Board or the Chairman`
  line `and Managing Director) serving in the employment immediately before the appointed day shall, in so`
  line `far as such officer or other employee is employed in connection with the undertakings which have`
  line `vested in the Company by virtue of this Act, become, as from the appointed day, an officer or, as the`
  line `case may be, other employee of the Company and shall hold his office or service therein by the same`
  line `tenure, at the same remuneration, upon the same terms and conditions, with the same obligations and`
  line `with the same rights and privileges as to leave, leave fare concession, welfare scheme, medical benefit`
  line `scheme, insurance, provident fund, other funds, retirement, voluntary retirement, gratuity and other`
  line `benefits as he would have held under the Reconstruction Bank if its undertakings had not vested in the`
  line `Company and shall continue to do so as an officer or, as the case may be, other employee of the`
  line `Company or until the expiry of a period of six months from the appointed day if such officer or other`
  line `employee opts not to continue to be the officer or other employee of the Company within such period.`
  line
  line `(2) Where an officer or other employee of the Reconstruction Bank opts under sub-section (1) not`
  line `to be in employment or service of the Company, such officer or other employee shall be deemed to have`
  line resigned.
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Industrial Disputes Act, 1947 (14 of 1947) in any`
  line `other law for the lime being in force, the transfer of the services of any officer or other employee of the`
  line `Reconstruction Bank to the Company shall not entitle such officer or other employee to any`
  line `compensation under this Act or under any other law for the time being in force and no such claim shall`
  line `be entertained by any court, tribunal or other authority.`
  line
  line `(4) The officers and other employees who have retired before the appointed day from the service of`
  line `the Reconstruction Bank and are entitled to any benefits, rights or privileges shall be entitled to receive`
  line `the same benefits, rights or privileges from the Company.`
  line
  line `(5) The trust of the provident fund or the gratuity fund of the Reconstruction Bank and any other`
  line `bodies created for the welfare of officers or employees would continue to discharge their functions in`
  line `the Company as was being done hitherto in the Reconstruction Bank and any tax exemption granted to`
  line `the provident fund or the gratuity fund would continue to be applied to the Company.`
  line
  line `(6) Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act or in the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956) or`
  line `in any other law for the time being in force or in the regulations of the Reconstruction Bank, no Director`
  line `of the Board, Chairman and Managing Director or any other person entitled to manage the whole or`
  line `substantial part of the business and affairs of the Reconstruction Bank shall be entitled to any`
  line `compensation against the Reconstruction Bank or the Company for the toss of office or for the`
  line `premature termination of any contract of management entered into by him with the Reconstruction`
  line Bank.
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (52345)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Concession, etc., to be deemed to have been granted to Company.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00046_199707_1613368563388&sectionId=52345&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00046_199707_1613368563388
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `With effect from the`
  line `appointed day, all fiscal and other concessions, licences, benefits, privileges and exemptions granted to the Reconstruction Bank in connection with the affairs and business of the Reconstruction Bank under`
  line `any law for the time being in force shall be deemed to have been granted to the Company.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (52346)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Tax exemption or benefit to continue to have effect.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00046_199707_1613368563388&sectionId=52346&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00046_199707_1613368563388
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained`
  line `in the Income-tax Act, 1961 (43 of 1961) or any other enactment for the time being in force relating to`
  line `tax or income, profits or gains, the Company shall not be liable to pay income-tax or any other tax for`
  line `a period of five years computed from the appointed day in respect of any income, profits or gains`
  line `derived, or any amount received by the Company.`
  line
  line `(2) The transfer and vesting of the undertakings or any part thereof in terms of section 3 shall not`
  line `be construed as a transfer within the meaning of the Income-tax At, 1961 (43 of 1961) for the purposes`
  line `of capital gains.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (52347)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Guarantee to be operative.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00046_199707_1613368563388&sectionId=52347&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00046_199707_1613368563388
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `Any guarantee given for or in favour of the Reconstruction Bank`
  line `with respect to any loan, lease finance or other assistance shall continue to be operative in relation to`
  line `the Company.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (52348)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Arrangement with Company on appointment of directors to prevail.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00046_199707_1613368563388&sectionId=52348&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00046_199707_1613368563388
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where any`
  line `arrangement entered into by the company with an industrial or other concern provides for the`
  line `appointment by the company of one or more directors of such concern, such provision and any`
  line `appointment of directors made in pursuance thereof shall be valid and effective notwithstanding`
  line `anything to the contrary contained in the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956) or in any other law for the`
  line `time being in force or in the memorandum, articles of association or any other instrument relating to`
  line `such concern, and any provision regarding share qualification, age limit, number of directorships,`
  line `removal from office of directors and such like conditions contained in any such law or instrument`
  line `aforesaid, shall not apply to any director appointed by the company in pursuance of the arrangement as`
  line aforesaid.
  line
  line `(2) Any director appointed in pursuance of sub-section (7) shall--`
  line
  line `(a) hold office during the pleasure of the company and may be removed or substituted by any`
  line `person by order in writing by the company;`
  line
  line `(b) not incur any obligation or liability by reason only of his being a director or for anything`
  line `done or omitted to be done in good faith in the discharge of his duties as a director or anything in`
  line `relation thereto;`
  line
  line `(c) not be liable to retirement by rotation and shall not be taken into account for computing the`
  line `number of directors liable to such retirement.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (52349)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Act 18 of 1891 to apply to the books of Company.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00046_199707_1613368563388&sectionId=52349&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00046_199707_1613368563388
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `The Company shall be deemed to be a`
  line `bank for the purposes of the Bankers' Books Evidence Act, 1891.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (52350)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Shares, bonds and debentures to be deemed to be approved securities.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00046_199707_1613368563388&sectionId=52350&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00046_199707_1613368563388
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line Notwithstanding
  line `anything contained in any other law for the time being in force, the shares, bonds and debentures of the`
  line `Company shall be deemed to be approved securities for the purposes of the Indian, Trusts Act, 1882 (2`
  line `of 1882) , the Insurance Act, 1938 (4 of 1938) ^1***.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words and figures "and the Banking Regulation Act, 1949(10 of 1949)" shall be omitted by Act 4 of 2013, s. 17 and`
  line `the Schedule (w.e.f. 18-1-2013).`
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (52351)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Substitution in Act, rules or regulations of company in place of the Reconstruction Bank.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00046_199707_1613368563388&sectionId=52351&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00046_199707_1613368563388
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `In every Act, rule or regulation in force on the appointed day,--`
  line
  line `(a) for the words "Industrial Reconstruction Bank of India", wherever they occur, the words`
  line `"Industrial Investment Bank of India Limited" shall be substituted;`
  line
  line `(b) for the words "Reconstruction Bank", wherever they occur, the words "Industrial Investment`
  line `Bank" shall be substituted.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (52352)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Repeal and saving of Act 62 of 1984.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00046_199707_1613368563388&sectionId=52352&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00046_199707_1613368563388
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) On the appointed day, the Industrial Reconstruction`
  line `Bank of India Act, 1984 shall stand repealed.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding the repeal of the Industrial Reconstruction Bank of India Act, 1984,--`
  line
  line `(a) the Company shall, so far as may be, comply with the provisions of Chapter VII of the Act`
  line `so repealed for any of the purposes related to the annual accounts and audit of the Reconstruction`
  line Bank;
  line
  line `(b) the provisions of Chapter VIII of the Act so repealed will continue to be applicable in respect`
  line `of the arrangements entered into by the Reconstruction Bank with an industrial concern under`
  line `section 18 thereof up to the appointed day and the Company will be entitled to act upon and enforce`
  line `the same as fully and effectually as if this Act had not been enacted.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (52353)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title Repealed.
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00046_199707_1613368563388&sectionId=52353&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00046_199707_1613368563388
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `[Insertion of new section 4A].--Rep. by the Repealing and Amending Act, 2001 (30 of 2001),`
  line `s. 2 and the First schedule (w.e.f. 2-9-2001).`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (52354)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Repeal and Saving.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00046_199707_1613368563388&sectionId=52354&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00046_199707_1613368563388
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Industrial Reconstruction Bank (Transfer of Undertakings and`
  line `Repeal) Ordinance, 1997 (Ord. 7 of 1997) is hereby repealed.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding such repeal, anything done or any action taken under the Ordinance so`
  line `repealed, shall tie deemed to have been done or taken under the corresponding provisions of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
